President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New Hampshire due to a severe winter storm that occurred in March 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Belknap and Carroll are eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide are also eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis. Albert Lewis has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.